HEADWORD: Plutus
<hw>Plu"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>The son of Jason and Ceres,
and the god of wealth. He was represented as bearing a cornucopia, and
as blind, because his gifts were bestowed without discrimination of
merit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluvial</ent>⟦br⟧
